<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_4ac03f40-6108-4836-bee3-cd2c132da94c" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>9.2.2</sptc><title id="_362906a1-d1a4-47fa-b720-27a1f1f3b3b1">Measurement of distances</title><archive-num>2019: 3.7.2.3</archive-num><subclause id="_889cdb8a-bd08-4416-bf16-65337f03c36a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_3eb73a1d-74b9-4bc0-9ff3-ff7c8f887c95">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The distance from any point on an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_6f519fb8-f6bb-4026-b4d5-a41016b4ce35" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref> of a building to an allotment boundary or another building is the distance to that point measured along a line at right angles from the allotment boundary or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_931fdaff-9f09-4a70-a05f-6c394b0907e3" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref> of the other building which intersects that point without being obstructed by a wall complying with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1848_1.9.0.xml#_263a5890-898c-4938-a6e8-4bd931480b0f" id="_8e3391d3-6686-4651-9c6d-8909273fc2b2" scope="local" type="clause">9.2.3</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_c9df1482-3b73-468f-87c2-519ba93f7694" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c6ec9e21-529b-4966-894e-2eec627dd01f">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Where a wall within a specified distance is <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_e282a83f-d129-4512-91d0-e459e80242b1" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> to comply with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1848_1.9.0.xml#_263a5890-898c-4938-a6e8-4bd931480b0f" id="_a95c1deb-061a-4be4-ace2-136f5e982ebe" scope="local" type="clause">9.2.3</xref>, only that part of the wall (including any openings) within the specified distance need be constructed in that manner (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/722_1.3.0.xml#_7274f320-a004-489f-8544-1cfe48f3da2c" id="_e7a88664-2b0f-4e1b-a1df-d0b48eb8c1b1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.2a</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/725_0.6.0.xml#_789d1da5-c4af-48e4-a756-f910b58bac71" id="_db8e2dd3-5f1a-4876-affe-061218f7f8da" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.2b</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/733_0.13.0.xml#_ea6e5535-8d4c-487b-bc1d-e8416224030f" id="_c4995fb5-b4c1-4c51-8a4e-d9cd396919a2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.2c</xref>).</p></subclause><subclause id="_90324724-3ed5-486a-a852-cae03e2ba235" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_5da07f07-5118-4a5b-900c-95693290d995">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Where the distance measured is between attached or detached buildings of different heights, the distance must be taken from the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_ec630fb4-1c7c-4c5b-9ec3-cee981d918bf" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref> with the highest elevation measured at right angles to a point that intersects the nearest part of a vertical projection above the adjacent building, excluding any eave overhang (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/734_0.12.0.xml#_1d045355-59d2-49c1-a8f2-b3026ee3e443" id="_642429a2-36a0-4208-81fe-583eaba4e283" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.2d</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/735_0.6.0.xml#_9850bcba-eb13-4fed-aa70-3744f12ae560" id="_32f45f9c-022b-46c1-9530-e59daf471588" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.2e</xref>).</p></subclause><subclause id="_4ec29bd4-2589-4620-a270-bd1a725475ae" outputclass="state-variation-insert" variation="SA" variation-type="INSERT"><title id="_edbe6c75-af85-4739-9a45-4272a5c7dc32">SA INSERT SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>The distance from any point on an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_3c06916e-ef2b-4e8c-91c6-22db09684992" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref>  of a building to a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/2464_0.6.0.xml#_58e3e6ab-77d3-470e-97bb-e60f6ed299d3" id="_27cd4689-9234-432f-8c31-60ec5dcf9e6c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">brush fence</xref> is measured in any direction from the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_6f87b6a5-fedd-47f9-af28-0e0d755ac595" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref>.</p></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/722_1.3.0.xml" id="_7274f320-a004-489f-8544-1cfe48f3da2c"><num/><title id="_daad5648-e75a-4b0b-b608-02be3a5d670b"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/725_0.6.0.xml" id="_789d1da5-c4af-48e4-a756-f910b58bac71"><num/><title id="_bf7ad31a-700a-4eca-8202-80276adac87d"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/733_0.13.0.xml" id="_ea6e5535-8d4c-487b-bc1d-e8416224030f"><num/><title id="_f2d65d2c-ae45-4350-a0ab-1c5a4935af10"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/734_0.12.0.xml" id="_1d045355-59d2-49c1-a8f2-b3026ee3e443"><num/><title id="_e5b73044-1608-4930-883b-f897ed88f5c7"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/735_0.6.0.xml" id="_9850bcba-eb13-4fed-aa70-3744f12ae560"><num/><title id="_ba422af4-f77d-403d-98b1-b84db3446103"/></image-reference></clause>